net.sf.jclec.mo.command

Class MaxObjectiveValue

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.jclec.mo.command.Command
      • net.sf.jclec.mo.command.MaxObjectiveValue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, net.sf.jclec.IConfigure, net.sf.jclec.JCLEC

    public class MaxObjectiveValue
extends Command
    This command calculates the maximum value of an objective function within the population. The given population is not modified during the execution of the command. The maximum value can be retrieved after the execution of the command using a getter method. The index of the objective function can be modified after the creation of the command, thus the execute() method will calculate the bounds considering the index currently stored.

    HISTORY:

    • (AR|JRR|SV, 1.0, March 2018) First release.

      • execute

        public void execute()
        Execute the command.

        This command calculates the maximum value for a given objective function. It considers the objective function whose position index is stored in index. The result will be stored in maxValue, so it can be then obtained using getMaxValue() method.
